@Santi good evening.  this is no rush but wanted to send this off while it was fresh in my mind.  I'm wondering if it would be a good idea to pause changing of the stations that supply FICs.   The current success rate of selling FICs is dismally low.  I know its because of Solana congestion, e.g. 2 tx and the second tx is failing. Not your fault.  And I know a few people have stopped trying to sell them until a fix is implemented.  It's just going to be a giant loss if people shipped their FICs to a station, coudn't sell them, then the station changes, and they have to ship them elsewhere again.

tl;dr Solana is FICing everyone.  Pls pause station changes.  Thank you!

p.s. for anyone that read this far - FIC sell success rate is higher when the U.S. is asleep and/or when priority fees are super low.  1) Redeem your certificates, 2) hit refresh at the top of the local market, 3) sell.   4) repeat until it goes through.
